From what I remember, Apache will send you a single chunk if you have it on, for example:<p><pre><code>  <? 
  echo &#x27;Hey<br>&#x27;;
  flush();
  ob_flush();
  sleep(20);
  echo &#x27;Bye&#x27;;
  ?>

  </code></pre>
Will send you &quot;Hey<br>Bye&quot; after 20sec instead of what you would expect (which does work with gzip off).<p>Besides, even if you manage to stream it, I imagine inflating partially received content is not trivial for the browser.
